{% from "components/popover/macro.njk" import popover %}
{% from "components/button/macro.njk" import button %}

<h2>Popover via the native Popover API</h2>
<p>The macro uses the HTML <code>popover</code> attribute; a
  trigger element declares <code>popovertarget</code> to open it.
  The browser handles open/close state, including Escape to close
  and light-dismiss on outside click.</p>

<p>
  {{ button({
    text: "Show details",
    attributes: { popovertarget: "pop-info" }
  }) }}
</p>

{% call popover({ id: "pop-info", label: "Details" }) %}
  <h3 style="margin-top: 0;">About this item</h3>
  <p>This is additional information anchored to the trigger
    button above. Press Escape or click outside to close.</p>
{% endcall %}

<h2>Manual popover</h2>
<p>A <code>popover="manual"</code> popover only closes when a
  script explicitly hides it — useful for state-driven UI.</p>

<p>
  {{ button({
    text: "Toggle manual popover",
    attributes: { popovertarget: "pop-manual" }
  }) }}
</p>

{% call popover({
  id: "pop-manual",
  popover: "manual",
  label: "Manual popover"
}) %}
  <p>I stay open until explicitly closed.</p>
  <button popovertarget="pop-manual" popovertargetaction="hide" class="button button-secondary">Close</button>
{% endcall %}
